# Back-end conventions

## File placement

- New REST handler → `src/app/controllers/{easy-genomics|aws-healthomics|nf-tower}/.../verb-name.lambda.ts`
- Business logic → matching `src/app/services/.../*-service.ts`
- New route → add Zod schema in `shared-lib`, entry in `shared-lib/src/app/openapi/route-schemas.ts`, regenerate OpenAPI

## Imports

Use `@BE/...` for back-end paths, `@SharedLib/...` for shared code.

## Authorization pattern

```typescript
import { validateLaboratoryManagerAccess, validateOrganizationAdminAccess } from '@BE/utils/auth-utils';
import { UnauthorizedAccessError } from '@easy-genomics/shared-lib/lib/app/utils/HttpError';

if (!(validateOrganizationAdminAccess(event, orgId) || validateLaboratoryManagerAccess(event, orgId, labId))) {
  throw new UnauthorizedAccessError();
}
```

## Services

Instantiate services at module scope (`const xService = new XService()`). DynamoDB access goes through service classes, not raw SDK in handlers.

## Infra

Lambda registration and IAM: `src/infra/constructs/lambda-construct.ts` and stacks under `src/infra/stacks/`. Changing a handler path may require infra + `route-schemas.ts` updates.
